@node MAIN "commandline.html"
     Command line options     Command line options  

Tag-o-Miga's command line is as follows:       
         	Amiga         	EDITFILE/A,CONFIG/K,ARGS/F          
         	DOS/Windows         	[/C config] editfile [args]          
         	Unix         	[-c config] editfile [args]        

These work as follows:  

@{"b"}EDITFILE@{"ub"} This contains the name of the file which contains the message being edited. For example, for Spot it is usually T:Spot.temp.  

@{"b"}CONFIG@{"ub"} This forces Tag-o-Miga to read its configuration from a different file. Using this option will override the platform-default configuration file.  

@{"b"}ARGS@{"ub"} Any addition arguments which your editor may require. This are inserted into the editor command string (see the preferences tool) in place of the @A sequence.  
	----------------------------------------
  

